RUMBUL • A quick walk around @madmike.123’s Superlight stadium truck dubbed “Rumbul”. In typical Mike Whiddett fashion it’s powered by a rowdy MadLab naturally aspirated 13b peripherally ported twin rotor pumping out 280hp. A considerable amount when the truck weighs a scant 1985lbs. The rear wheels are driven by a buff Mendeola 4 speed transmission and the long travel arms and triple bypass King shocks ensure it can handle the terrain and even some pretty big jumps. It’s been a ton of fun working on this truck with Mike’s MadLab team and soon you’ll get to see some RAD footage from our recent trip to the UK. Stay tuned!

#TheFREK • After many years of putting my passion project at @throtl together with the team, @quinnmclark and I got to experience what our custom built rear wheel drive Honda Civic feels like at the track and skid pad. The car is rad, it absolutely rips honestly, and the build is beyond stout. But, I didn’t anticipate how much goes into dialing in a car of this nature after it’s “a car”. There is so much custom fab work and mix matching of parts that the geometry and balance are not what you’d expect. After a full day at @gridlifeofficial we made heaps of progress and we’re able to leave Willow Springs feeling pretty good about the day, even though we faced MANY challenges. The throtl YouTube video will showcase the trials & tribulations as well as quite a bit of fun. We even let our boy @larry_chen_foto take’er out for some skids, which he documented for his YT channel! What a great day and I’m looking forward to the next one in anticipation! 😁👍🏼

#throtl #rwdcivic #hondacivic #ek9 #k20 #rwd #hatch #ek9typer #k20turbo

Old or New(er)? • Seeing a four door Nissan Skyline GT-R in person is a rare occasion. Yesterday, at @japaneseclassiccarshow, was the first time, other than the Nissan Zama Museum, that I saw both the 1969 Nissan Skyline GT-R and the 40th Anniversary 1998 Nissan Skyline Autech Version in the same place. It was a cool sight for me to see and take in. I’m honored to be the owner and care taker of this special late model automobile and I wish I could explain the joy it brings me every time I twist the key and hear the legendary RB26 engine come to life. To many, the GT-R is “just a car”. To me it has become a lifestyle.

R’s DAY 23 • This was one of the BEST days of my entire life. 😀 I attended with the intention of hanging out with the GT-R community, looking over some cars and to be with friends. Never with the intention of actually pushing the elderly Autech R33 GT-R to ten-tenths around the Streets of Willow circuit. R’s Day organizers @root_beer_26_jack and his wife @miss_frs insisted I get out on track. Once I buckled my helmet, gripped the wheel and mashed the pedal to the floor, I immediately realized the car was able to be pushed. I mean, there’s just something about a GT-R that instills confidence and desire in the driver to go faster and do more. I don’t know, it’s hard to explain. But, this is my third time taking an old GT-R on a circuit and I’ve gotten the same rush of inspiration and satisfaction each time. It’s not like anything I’ve ever experienced. I’ve really got the bug to get back out there now. Maybe it’s time to get the R32 prepped for @nissanchallenge 2024?

I owe a debt of gratitude to many people for that day and many of them were around me throughout it, including my rock @miss_courtney_day. ❤️ 

#throtl #Nissan #skylinegtr #skyline #r33 #autechversion #autechgtr #rsday #r33gtr
